's University Belfast"}],". My research centers on building safe, reliable, and secure artificial intelligence for intelligent transport systems, with a particular focus on two core pillars:"]}],["$","ul",null,{"children":[["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Run-time Monitoring & Introspection:"}]," Developing mechanisms to assess and ensure the reliability of perception modules (e.g., LiDAR-based 3D object detection) under uncertainties and adverse conditions."]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Safe & Resilient Cooperative Autonomy:"}]," Building verifiable and interoperable frameworks for Connected and Automated Vehicles (CAVs) in real-world environments."]}]]}],["$","p",null,{"children":["Prior to joining QUB, I was a Postdoctoral Research Fellow at ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"WMG, University of Warwick"}],", where I worked on EU-funded projects (such as ",["$","em",null,{"children":"EVENTS"}]," and ",["$","em",null,{"children":"Hi-Drive"}],") to integrate self-assessment and perception frameworks into real-world automated driving pipelines. I completed my Ph.D. in Engineering from the University of Warwick (supervised by Dr. Roger Woodman and Prof. Mehrdad Dianati)."]}],["$","p",null,{"children":"I hold a Master's and Bachelor's degree in Computer Engineering from Middle East Technical University (METU NCC)."}],["$","p",null,{"style":{"marginTop":"1rem","fontStyle":"italic","background":"var(--bg-secondary)","padding":"1rem","borderRadius":"var(--radius-sm)"},"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Prospective Students:"}]," I am actively looking for self-motivated PhD students and researchers interested in safe and reliable AI for autonomous systems. Please feel free to drop me an email!"]}]]}]]}],["$","section",null,{"id":"news","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"page_sectionTitle__hzsAh","children":"Recent News"}],["$","ul",null,{"className":"page_newsList__ezGoX","children":[["$","li",null,